Correlate update and implementation for enumerable convention
body:
This facelifts Correlate relation and adds implementation for enumerables (i.e. nested loops, nested loops outer, nested loops semi, nested loops anti).
In current PR correlation/de-correlation should be intact (as much as it is possible). Special handling in planner/sql parser will be updated later.

A new planner config variable is added: forceDecorrelate=true(default)/false. By default planner still tries to de-correlate a lot, however for testing purposes de-correlation can be disabled. The setting might be removed if de-correlation is converted to cost-based-rule.

body:
Detects the version of mongod to determine which kind of intermediate
result to utilize.

For versions 2.6+, a Cursor result will be returned form the
DBCollection otherwise a AggregationOutput result is returned.

An Iterator<DBObject> object is retrieved from the intermediate result 
and returned by MongoTable.aggregate.

Updated dependency in for mongo-java-driver in master/mongodb/pom.xml:

```
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.mongodb</groupId>
  <artifactId>mongo-java-driver</artifactId>
  <version>2.12.3</version>
</dependency>
```
